ult) .elementor-drop-cap-letter{width:1em;height:1em}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap{float:left;text-align:center;line-height:1;font-size:50px}.elementor-widget-text-editor .elementor-drop-cap-letter{display:inline-block}<\/style>\t\t\t\t<h1><\/h1>\r\n<strong>Erasmus+<\/strong> is the <strong>European Union&#8217;s flagship program<\/strong> supporting education, training, youth, and sport across Europe. With an estimated budget of \u20ac26.2 billion, it nearly doubled the funding compared to its predecessor program (2014-2020). The new 2021-2027 program prioritizes social inclusion, the green and digital transitions, and enhancing youth participation in democratic processes. Here is Abroadin&#8217;s comprehensive guide to apply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship in seven steps.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIn this guide:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Explore Erasmus Mundus Programs<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Confirm Your Eligibility to Apply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Create Your Application Checklist<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Familiarize Yourself with the Erasmus Mundus Platform<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Consider Application Deadlines and Submission<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Prepare for Interviews to Apply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Monitor Your Application Status<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Conclusion<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>1. Explore Erasmus Mundus Programs<\/h2>\r\n<strong>Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters<\/strong> are esteemed international master&#8217;s programs collaboratively designed and delivered by a consortium of higher education institutions.\r\n\r\nThese programs typically involve a minimum of three institutions from at least three different countries, along with multiple associated partners from both academic and non-academic realms. They encompass various elements such as study periods, research, traineeships, thesis preparation, and defense.\r\n\r\nStart to apply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship by visiting <a href=\"https:\/\/www.eacea.ec.europa.eu\/scholarships\/erasmus-mundus-catalogue_en\">the official website<\/a> and exploring the programs available that align with your academic and career aspirations.\r\n\r\nExplore the specifics of each program of interest by checking its website. Understand its objectives, participating universities, structure, and requirements thoroughly.\r\n\r\nUpon enrollment, you have the opportunity to earn either a joint degree (a single degree certificate issued by at least two higher education institutions) or multiple degrees (at least two-degree certificates issued by two higher education institutions within the consortium).\r\n\r\nThese specifics are outlined in detail upon signing a study agreement with the relevant <strong>Erasmus Mundus Joint Master<\/strong> at the outset of your studies.\r\n\r\nApply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship involves directly applying to the institution overseeing your chosen program. Navigate through the program catalog to find details about the updates available.\r\n\r\nNote that a new cohort of selected Erasmus Mundus Masters is added to the list each year. Typically, applications for courses commencing in the subsequent academic year should be submitted between October and January.\r\n\r\n<span style=\"background-color: #99ccff;\">Each master&#8217;s website provides comprehensive details regarding the course of study, participating universities, entry requirements, and the application process, both with and without scholarships.<\/span>\r\n\r\nif you want to know about <a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/4-sources-to-find-scholarships-in-europe\/\">Scholarships in Europe<\/a> read this article:\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"sec8XoEdMB\"><a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/4-sources-to-find-scholarships-in-europe\/\">4 Sources to Find Scholarships in Europe<\/a><\/blockquote><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;4 Sources to Find Scholarships in Europe&#8221; &#8212; Abroadin \" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/4-sources-to-find-scholarships-in-europe\/embed\/#?secret=gPRgiEhGuj#?secret=sec8XoEdMB\" data-secret=\"sec8XoEdMB\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe>\r\n<h2>2. Confirm Your Eligibility to Apply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship<\/h2>\r\nBefore proceeding with applications, carefully review the eligibility criteria for each program to ensure alignment with your academic background, language proficiency, and any other specific prerequisites.\r\n\r\nConsider programs that best resonate with your goals, interests, and eligibility. To qualify for these chosen programs, certain criteria must be met, including:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>A first degree equivalent to 180 credits or 180 ECTS from an internationally recognized university or college.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>A minimum of two years of practitioner experience in the field of human rights, encompassing regular employment, internships, or voluntary work.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>A minimum English language qualification is equivalent to English B\/English 6 at the upper secondary level or an equivalent level through internationally recognized tests such as<strong> TOEFL<\/strong> and <strong>IELTS<\/strong>.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nAlso, the Erasmus Mundus Scholarship requirements include:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>A letter of motivation within 800 words.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>A residency certificate.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>All academic transcripts.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Two letters of recommendation.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>A research project or study plan.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Limited stay (not exceeding 12 months in the last 5 years) in any eligible European country at the time of application submission.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>No previous receipt of similar scholarships under the Erasmus Mundus Action 2 project.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nFor updated information, always refer to the official website of the Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters and also the Abroadin blog.\r\n\r\n<img fetchpriority=\"high\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2336\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/robert-bye-4hcpIbqQM8c-unsplash-300x225.webp\" alt=\"erasmus mundus scholarship\" width=\"1090\" height=\"817\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/robert-bye-4hcpIbqQM8c-unsplash-300x225.webp 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/robert-bye-4hcpIbqQM8c-unsplash-1024x768.webp 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/robert-bye-4hcpIbqQM8c-unsplash-768x576.webp 768w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/robert-bye-4hcpIbqQM8c-unsplash-1536x1152.webp 1536w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/robert-bye-4hcpIbqQM8c-unsplash-2048x1536.webp 2048w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1090px) 100vw, 1090px\" \/>\r\n<h2>3. Create Your Application Checklist<\/h2>\r\nPrepare a checklist for each program, including academic transcripts, letters of recommendation, personal statements, and any other required documents.\r\n\r\nAdditionally, ensure you provide the following documents crucial for the ranking process conducted by the Joint Admission Committee of the EMHRPP:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Official transcript of records in English.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Motivation letter in English, well-structured and written in clear and concise language, using the assigned form.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Curriculum Vitae (CV).<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Two letters of recommendation.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n<span style=\"background-color: #99ccff;\">Personalize your statements for each program, emphasizing your passion, relevant experiences, and alignment with program goals. Highlight pertinent academic or professional achievements.<\/span>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>4. Familiarize Yourself with the Erasmus Mundus Platform<\/h2>\r\nNavigate through the application process and gather all necessary documents and information beforehand. Follow these steps to apply for the scholarship:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Visit <a href=\"https:\/\/www.eacea.ec.europa.eu\/scholarships\/erasmus-mundus-catalogue_en\">the official Erasmus+ website<\/a>.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Click on &#8220;Opportunities,&#8221; then &#8220;Opportunities for Individuals,&#8221; followed by &#8220;Opportunities for Students,&#8221; and finally, &#8220;Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters Degrees.&#8221;<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Browse through the program catalog and select your desired course.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Submit your application directly to the course coordinator.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>5. Consider Application Deadlines and Submission<\/h2>\r\nMark the deadlines for each program on your calendar, noting variations between programs. Key dates include:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Application round opens: October 16, 2024<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Application deadline: December 1, 2024<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Supporting documentation deadline: December 15, 2024<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Admissions results published: March 18, 2025<\/li>\r\n \t<li>The late Admission round is open between December 16, 2024, and January 31, 2025<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nGiven the competitive nature of the Erasmus Mundus Scholarship, consider the following tips to enhance your application:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li>Submit an error-free application.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Ensure you meet all requirements.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Perform well in the interview.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Maintain a strong academic record.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Attain a favorable English proficiency test score.<\/li>\r\n \t<li>Submit an impressive scholarship essay or cover letter.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>6. Prepare for Interviews to Apply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship<\/h2>\r\nAccording to the selection policy of Erasmus Mundus Scholarships, only three candidates are selected from each country.\r\n\r\nShould there be another high-achieving candidate from those countries, they will be placed on the reserved list in case the selected candidate withdraws from the same country.\r\n\r\nIn instances where applicants are equally qualified, preference will be given to under-represented genders.\r\n\r\nErasmus Mundus Scholarship applications are evaluated based on two key criteria:\r\n<ul>\r\n \t<li><strong>Academic Evaluation:<\/strong> Your academic performance is a crucial factor in assessing eligibility. Aim for a strong academic record.<\/li>\r\n \t<li><strong>Interview:<\/strong> Following successful academic evaluation, an interview will be conducted via video conference.<\/li>\r\n<\/ul>\r\nUpon selection for interviews, it&#8217;s crucial to thoroughly research the program and practice responses to common interview questions.\r\n\r\nKeep in mind that an email will be sent to all applicants regarding their selection for the scholarship program alongside their admissions to the university. The <strong>Erasmus Mundus Scholarships<\/strong> are awarded to 22 eligible candidates every year.\r\n\r\n<img decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignnone wp-image-2337\" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/back-view-medium-shot-two-teenage-girls-hugging-300x200.webp\" alt=\"erasmus mundus joint masters\" width=\"1060\" height=\"706\" srcset=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/back-view-medium-shot-two-teenage-girls-hugging-300x200.webp 300w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/back-view-medium-shot-two-teenage-girls-hugging-1024x683.webp 1024w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/back-view-medium-shot-two-teenage-girls-hugging-768x513.webp 768w, https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/05\/back-view-medium-shot-two-teenage-girls-hugging-1536x1025.webp 1536w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1060px) 100vw, 1060px\" \/>\r\n<h2>7. Monitor Your Application Status<\/h2>\r\nStay proactive by monitoring the status of your applications through the Erasmus Mundus portal. Respond promptly to any requests for additional information or interviews.\r\n\r\nIf available, consider enrolling in a mentorship program to guide you through the Erasmus Mundus scholarship application process. Fill out the mentorship enrollment form and follow the provided steps to access personalized advice, workshops, and resources.\r\n\r\nIn the meantime, remember to express gratitude to your recommenders and interviewers for their support. As needed, seek further guidance from mentors or professors.\r\n\r\nWhile awaiting scholarship decisions, maintain a positive outlook. Continue pursuing other opportunities and stay engaged in your academic and professional endeavors.\r\n\r\nBy diligently following these steps, you&#8217;ll be well-prepared to apply for <strong>Erasmus Mundus scholarship<\/strong> and enhance your chances of success.\r\n\r\nif you want to know more about <a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/erasmus-mundus-program-emjmd-step-by-step-guide\/\">Erasmus Mundus Program<\/a> read this article:\r\n\r\n<blockquote class=\"wp-embedded-content\" data-secret=\"Ux6b27shji\"><a href=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/erasmus-mundus-program-emjmd-step-by-step-guide\/\">Erasmus Mundus Program + EMJMD Step-by-Step Guide<\/a><\/blockquote><iframe class=\"wp-embedded-content\" sandbox=\"allow-scripts\" security=\"restricted\" style=\"position: absolute; clip: rect(1px, 1px, 1px, 1px);\" title=\"&#8220;Erasmus Mundus Program + EMJMD Step-by-Step Guide&#8221; &#8212; Abroadin \" src=\"https:\/\/abroadin.com\/blog\/erasmus-mundus-program-emjmd-step-by-step-guide\/embed\/#?secret=4TJLx7oiRc#?secret=Ux6b27shji\" data-secret=\"Ux6b27shji\" width=\"500\" height=\"282\" frameborder=\"0\" marginwidth=\"0\" marginheight=\"0\" scrolling=\"no\"><\/iframe>\r\n<h2><\/h2>\r\n<h2>Conclusion<\/h2>\r\nApply for Erasmus Mundus scholarship requires careful planning, attention to detail, and perseverance. Candidates can increase their chances of success by thoroughly understanding the programs, meeting eligibility criteria, submitting well-crafted applications, and preparing for interviews.\r\n\r\nIf you want to take the latest updates on Erasmus Mundus Joint Masters and many other available scholarships from around the world, just enter your email address in the field below and press subscribe button to receive Abroadin\u2019s guides and tips in your mailbox.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nResources:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.emhrpp.com\/how-to-apply\">https:\/\/www.emhrpp.com\/how-to-apply<\/a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https:\/\/erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu\/about-erasmus\/what-is-erasmus\">https:\/\/erasmus-plus.ec.europa.eu\/about-erasmus\/what-is-erasmus<\/a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.aeccglobal.com.np\/blog\/erasmus-mundus-scholarship\">https:\/\/www.aeccglobal.com.np\/blog\/erasmus-mundus-scholarship<\/a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/pulse\/erasmus-mundus-scholarships-step-by-step-guide-kohort-m7wac\">https:\/\/www.linkedin.com\/pulse\/erasmus-mundus-scholarships-step-by-step-guide-kohort-m7wac<\/a>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-93817f9 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"93817f9\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;jet_parallax_layout_list&quot;:[],&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-da1fcbb\" data-id=\"da1fcbb\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-ee5e7f4 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"ee5e7f4\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"